<p>Last, but not least, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/ghammadi">Guillaume Hammadi</a> drew this amazing illustration that summarises the talk:</p>
<blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en-gb"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Progressive image <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/rendering?src=hash">#rendering</a> by <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/jmperezperez">@jmperezperez</a> at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/cssconfau">@cssconfau</a> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/hashtag/cssconfau16?src=hash">#cssconfau16</a> <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://t.co/pKtcWWvjVL">pic.twitter.com/pKtcWWvjVL</a></p>&mdash; guillaume hammadi (@ghammadi) <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://twitter.com/ghammadi/status/803830326657249282">30 November 2016</a></blockquote>
